# Geometry Plotter

A drawing tool for artists to compose with geometric shapes and export as SVG.

![Demo](plotter.html)

## Features

✨ **6 Shape Types**
- Rectangle (with rounded corners)
- Circle
- Ellipse
- Polygon (3-12 sides)
- Line

🎨 **Visual Properties**
- Fill color
- Stroke color & width
- Opacity control
- Position & size

🖱️ **Interactive Interface**
- Click to create shapes
- Drag to reposition
- Resize handles on selection
- Layer list with thumbnails

📤 **SVG Export**
- Clean, standards-compliant SVG
- White background
- Ready for editors (Illustrator, Figma, Inkscape)

## Usage

Open in browser:
```bash
open src/art/geometry/plotter.html
```

Or serve:
```bash
npx live-server src/art/geometry
```

## Controls

| Action | Method |
|--------|--------|
| Create shape | Select tool + click canvas |
| Select shape | Click shape or layer item |
| Move shape | Drag selected shape |
| Resize | Drag corner handle |
| Delete | Delete key or layer × button |
| Undo | Ctrl+Z |
| Export SVG | Header button |

## Properties Panel

Selected shapes show:
- Position X/Y
- Fill/Stroke colors
- Stroke width (0-10px)
- Opacity (0-100%)

Shape-specific controls:
- **Rectangle**: width, height, corner radius
- **Circle/Ellipse**: radius/radii
- **Polygon**: sides count, radius
- **Line**: endpoint coordinates

## Files

- `plotter.html` - Application UI (8KB)
- `plotter.js` - Drawing engine (22KB)
- `plotter.test.ts` - Export validation tests

## Test Status

✅ 673 tests passing

## Browser Support

Modern browsers: Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge

## License

Part of Nexus bootstrap - artistic tool experiments
