### Features

**Drag & Drop Interface**
- Drop JSON histogram files onto the page
- Supports multiple files simultaneously

**Visual Comparison**
- Side-by-side before/after panels
- RGB channels overlaid with transparency
- Canvas-based rendering for performance

**Statistics Display**
- Mean value
- Standard deviation
- Per-channel histogram distribution

### Data Format

```json
{
  "file": "image_name.png",
  "before": {
    "mean": 85.3,
    "stdDev": 42.1,
    "histograms": {
      "red": [12, 45, 89, ...],
      "green": [15, 48, 92, ...],
      "blue": [10, 42, 86, ...]
    }
  },
  "after": { ... }
}
```

### Usage

```bash
open tools/analyze/histogram_viewer.html
```

Then drag your histogram JSON files onto the page.

